-- Nexen Inc sells $1.5 billion in 2 parts: source
-- 
-- Tue May 1, 2007 5:50pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/01/us-nexen-debt-sale-idUSN0125829220070501

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Nexen Inc. NXY.TO, the Canadian oil producer, on Tuesday sold $1.5 billion of debt in two parts, said a source familiar with the deal. 

 The sale included $250 million of 5.65 percent 10-year notes priced at 99.68 to yield 5.692 percent or 1.05 percentage points more than U.S. Treasuries. Included in the sale were $1.25 billion of 6.40 percent 30-year bonds priced at 99.56 to yield 6.433 percent or 1.60 percentage points over Treasuries. The joint lead managers of the sale were Banc of America Securities, Citigroup Global Markets and Deutsche Bank, the source said.